cs.DL, cs.IR, cs.LIB, cs.CY, cs.CR

The paper discusses a new indicator of journal citation impact, which is relevant to the fields of digital libraries (cs.DL) and information retrieval (cs.IR). It also mentions the need to take into account the extent to which a database used for the assessment covers the field's literature, which is relevant to the field of digital libraries (cs.DL). The paper further develops Eugene Garfield's notions of a field's 'citation potential', which is relevant to the field of library and information science (cs.LIB). The paper also discusses the differences in citation potential between journals within the same subject category, which is relevant to the fields of cryptography (cs.CR) and cybernetics (cs.CY).
